{
  "dialogueGraphs": [
    {
      "id": "DG_PLAQUE_SP01",
      "sceneId": "SCN-016",
      "startNodeId": "N_INTRO",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "N_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The admin lobby smells like paper that gave up.\nA faded asset plaque hangs at shoulder height, half covered in contractor stickers that promise they were \u201ctemporary.\u201d",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "key": "paperwork.assetIdRecorded",
              "op": "==",
              "value": false
            }
          ],
          "next": "PC_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_MAIN",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_READ",
              "text": "look \u2014 Read the plaque.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_READ"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_PEEL",
              "text": "use \u2014 Peel back the stickers.",
              "next": "N_PEEL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_STEP",
              "text": "leave \u2014 Step away.",
              "next": "N_LEAVE_EARLY"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_READ",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You tilt until the overhead lights stop reflecting.\nMost of the lettering is scuffed into bureaucracy: SERIAL, DIVISION, RESPONSIBLE PARTY\u2014then a sticker blocks the one line that matters.",
          "next": "PC_AFTER_LOOK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_AFTER_LOOK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_PEEL_2",
              "text": "use \u2014 Peel back the stickers.",
              "next": "N_PEEL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_BACK_MAIN",
              "text": "look \u2014 Look again from a distance.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_STEP_2",
              "text": "leave \u2014 Step away.",
              "next": "N_LEAVE_EARLY"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PEEL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The adhesive resists like it has a contract.\nA corner lifts, then another, and the sticker comes off in angry little flakes.",
          "next": "N_PEEL_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PEEL_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Under it: an older sticker.\nUnder that: marker ink that tried to become official.\nUnder that: the original stamped handle, still clean where nobody\u2019s touched it in years.",
          "next": "N_REVEAL_SP01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_REVEAL_SP01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "SP-01.",
          "next": "PC_DECIDE_SP01"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_DECIDE_SP01",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_RECORD",
              "text": "use \u2014 Record \u201cSP-01\u201d in the closure paperwork.",
              "next": "N_RECORDING"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_DOUBLECHECK",
              "text": "ask \u2014 Double-check: is this the asset handle or a subcomponent tag?",
              "next": "N_DOUBLECHECK"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_OLEA_STANDARDS",
              "text": "ask \u2014 Apply OLEA naming standards to confirm the format.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "player.factions",
                  "op": "in",
                  "value": "OLEA"
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_OLEA_CONFIRM"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_NEWER",
              "text": "look \u2014 Keep looking for a newer label.",
              "next": "N_SCAN_LABELS"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_BACK_TO_MAIN_2",
              "text": "look \u2014 Look at the plaque again from the start.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_NOW",
              "text": "leave \u2014 Leave it for now.",
              "next": "N_LEAVE_LATE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DOUBLECHECK",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The plaque doesn\u2019t clarify. It just sits there with the confidence of something that will outlast your audit cycle.\n\u201cSP-01\u201d is stamped deeper than the other text, which is usually how the \u201creal\u201d label behaves.",
          "next": "PC_AFTER_DOUBLECHECK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_AFTER_DOUBLECHECK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_RECORD_2",
              "text": "use \u2014 Record \u201cSP-01\u201d in the closure paperwork.",
              "next": "N_RECORDING"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_NEWER_2",
              "text": "look \u2014 Keep looking for a newer label.",
              "next": "N_SCAN_LABELS"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_BACK_DECIDE",
              "text": "look \u2014 Look back at the handle.",
              "next": "PC_DECIDE_SP01"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_3",
              "text": "leave \u2014 Leave it for now.",
              "next": "N_LEAVE_LATE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_OLEA_CONFIRM",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "OLEA site handles, when they\u2019re being consistent, follow a short prefix plus an ordinal.\nConsistency is the tell: this is the only thing on the plaque that looks like it was meant to be referenced in a form.",
          "next": "PC_AFTER_OLEA"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_AFTER_OLEA",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_RECORD_3",
              "text": "use \u2014 Record \u201cSP-01\u201d in the closure paperwork.",
              "next": "N_RECORDING"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_NEWER_3",
              "text": "look \u2014 Keep looking for a newer label.",
              "next": "N_SCAN_LABELS"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_BACK_DECIDE_2",
              "text": "look \u2014 Look back at the handle.",
              "next": "PC_DECIDE_SP01"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_4",
              "text": "leave \u2014 Leave it for now.",
              "next": "N_LEAVE_LATE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SCAN_LABELS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You scan the remaining stickers: vendor logos, a phone number with too many digits, a \u201cRevised\u201d date with no year.\nNothing overrides the stamped handle. Nothing even tries.",
          "next": "PC_AFTER_SCAN"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_AFTER_SCAN",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_RECORD_4",
              "text": "use \u2014 Record \u201cSP-01\u201d in the closure paperwork.",
              "next": "N_RECORDING"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_BACK_DECIDE_3",
              "text": "look \u2014 Look back at the handle.",
              "next": "PC_DECIDE_SP01"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_5",
              "text": "leave \u2014 Step away.",
              "next": "N_LEAVE_LATE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_RECORDING",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You write it down exactly as stamped, because handwriting is where blame hides.\nThe pen squeaks on the form like it objects to being useful.\n\nThe plaque stays on the wall, looking newly exposed and vaguely offended.",
          "next": "END_RECORDED"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_RECORDED",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "record_asset_id",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "paperwork.assetIdRecorded",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "paperwork.assetId",
              "action": "set",
              "value": "SP-01"
            },
            {
              "key": "paperwork.completeness",
              "action": "increment",
              "value": 1
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LEAVE_EARLY",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You leave the plaque where it is\u2014half labeled, half forgotten, fully official either way.",
          "next": "END_LEAVE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LEAVE_LATE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You step back. The plaque returns to being background infrastructure, which is how most problems get to grow.",
          "next": "END_LEAVE"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_LEAVE",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
